# Frontend Asset Minification

Minification is handled by npm scripts defined in the root `package.json`.
**Never edit `.min.js` or `.min.css` files directly** — always edit the source file and rebuild.

## Tools

| Asset | Tool | npm script |
|---|---|---|
| JS | `terser` | `minify-js` / `minify-js-all` |
| CSS | `clean-css-cli` | `minify-css` / `minify-css-all` |

## Commands

```bash
# Single file (output written to <file>.min.js / <file>.min.css automatically)
npm run minify-js -- public/libraries/resources/app.js
npm run minify-js -- public/layouts/basic/modules/Base/resources/Header.js

npm run minify-css -- public/layouts/basic/modules/Base/resources/style.css

# Whole tree (use after bulk changes)
npm run minify-js-all
npm run minify-css-all
```

## Workflow rule

After editing any non-minified `.js` or `.css` file under `public/`, run the corresponding
single-file minify command and commit both the source and the `.min.*` file together.
